Sampling area approximately 250m upstream of bicycle path bridge crossing at Fontaine River. Access trail via cemetery parking (gated: key AF) then follow bicycle path N for about 1 km till reach bridge crossing. Cross bridge and descend to northern bank of river then follow upstream through forest until site. Site at bend with rocky bank on N side of river. Rocks coated with sludgy dark mineral deposits that can be scrapped off (thick). Some beaver activity 100m upstream of site. If continues, we will consider moving site to riffle just upstream of bridge in subsequent years to be further away from this influence.
